Research has shown, students acquire literacy most efficiently in their native language.An education system that overly glorifies a foreign language is fated to fail. The Constitution of Kenya 2010 recognises Kiswahili as the national language at Article 7. It also recognises it, besides English, as an official language.
It tasks the state with the responsibility of promoting and protecting the diversity of language of the people of Kenya and promoting the development and use of indigenous languages, including in instruction.



